Chidibube Okeoma, Owerri The Governor of Imo State, Hope Uzodinma, has approved the appointment of nine special advisers into his government. The Chief Press Secretary to the governor, Oguwike Nwachukwu, announced the appointments in a statement in Owerri, the state capital. According to the statement, the governor appointed Rubby Emele, SA, Local Government and chieftaincy Affairs; Tina Ude, SA, Sustainable Development Goals and Humanitarian Services; Bathos Nwadike, SA, Political; Pat Ekeji, Special Adviser, Strategy and Development; and Macdonald Ebere, SA/Managing Director, Environmental Transformation Commission. Others are Innocent Ikpa, SA/General Manager, Owerri Capital Development Authority; Dominic Uzowurum, SA, Inter-Party Affairs; Amaka Okafor, SA, Electronic Media; and Prof. Henry Njoku, Chief Technical Adviser/Coordinator, Economic Development and Rehabilitation Council. The statement noted that the appointments take immediate effect. Copyright PUNCH.
